<subSubSection id="C349651EFFD4FF8AB5B9FDD2FCACFC27" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD4FF8AB5B9FDD2FEBEFDEC" blockId="24.[189,310,567,593]" box="[189,310,567,593]" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">
<heading id="D0A481F9FFD4FF8AB5B9FDD2FEBEFDEC" bold="true" box="[189,310,567,593]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD4FF8AB5B9FDD2FEBEFDEC" bold="true" box="[189,310,567,593]" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD4FF8AB5B9FD80FCACFC27" blockId="24.[188,1399,613,922]" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">
The female is closest to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD4FF8AB72AFD83FD11FDC2" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[558,665,613,640]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbus">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD4FF8AB72AFD83FD11FDC2" box="[558,665,613,640]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">S. gibbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of the head and sculpture of the body, but differs from this species by the less elevated vertex with distance from top of head to upper margin of lateral ocellus approximately two lateral ocellar diameters as seen in frontal view (vs ca 3), the sparser punctate metasoma with almost impunctate marginal zones on T1 and T2 (distinctly punctate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD4FF8AB1A9FD2AFA9FFD54" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1197,1303,719,745]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbus">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD4FF8AB1A9FD2AFA9FFD54" box="[1197,1303,719,745]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">S. gibbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and on average smaller body length 
<quantity id="4CAB9B70FFD4FF8AB70BFD17FD1DFCB0" box="[527,661,754,781]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.5">7.5–10 mm</quantity>
(vs 
<quantity id="4CAB9B70FFD4FF8AB7C3FD17FCB4FCB0" box="[711,828,754,781]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="11.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="7.0">7–15 mm</quantity>
). We have not studied the male, but according to the description of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B64FFD4FF8AB490FCF0FDDFFC8D" author="Bluthgen P." box="[404,599,789,816]" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" pagination="23 - 112" refId="ref17172" refString="Bluthgen P. 1927. Beitrage zur Systematik der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. III. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 53 (1 / 3): 23 - 112." type="journal article" year="1927">Blüthgen (1927)</bibRefCitation>
it is similar to that of the Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD4FF8AB113FCF3FACCFC8D" authority="Smith, 1853" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[1047,1348,789,816]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alternatus">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD4FF8AB113FCF3FB24FC92" box="[1047,1196,789,816]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">S. alternatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B64FFD4FF8AB1B7FCF0FACCFC8D" author="Smith F." box="[1203,1348,789,816]" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" refId="ref19123" refString="Smith F. 1853 Catalogue of Hymenopterous Insects in the Collection of the British Museum. Andrenidae and Apidae. Vol. 1. Printed by order of the Trustees, London. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 20858" type="book" year="1853">Smith, 1853</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD4FF8AB5BAFCDCFD9FFCEE" authority="Thomson, 1870" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1870" box="[190,535,825,851]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulatus">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD4FF8AB5BAFCDCFEDFFCEE" box="[190,343,825,851]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">S. reticulatus</emphasis>
Thomson, 1870
</taxonomicName>
owing to similar sculpture, shapes of antennal tyloid area and gonostylus (tyloids of 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD4FF8AB440FCB9FE56FCCB" authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1927" box="[324,478,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lasimensis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD4FF8AB440FCB9FE56FCCB" box="[324,478,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">S. lasimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more developed and semicircular across basal 1/5–⅓ of ventral flagellar surface vs 1/7–1/ 
<quantity id="4CAB9B70FFD4FF8AB478FC9AFE2DFC24" box="[380,421,895,922]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD4FF8AB4A8FC9AFDC8FC24" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[428,576,895,921]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alternatus">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD4FF8AB4A8FC9AFDC8FC24" box="[428,576,895,921]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">S. alternatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD4FF8AB77DFC9AFC9BFC24" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1870" box="[633,787,895,921]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulatus">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD4FF8AB77DFC9AFC9BFC24" box="[633,787,895,921]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="98">S. reticulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
