<subSubSection id="C349651EFFD5FF88B5B9FEEDFEEBFD1C" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD5FF8BB5B9FEEDFE1BFE9E" blockId="25.[189,403,264,291]" box="[189,403,264,291]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">
<heading id="D0A481F9FFD5FF8BB5B9FEEDFE1BFE9E" bold="true" box="[189,403,264,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD5FF8BB5B9FEEDFE1BFE9E" bold="true" box="[189,403,264,291]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Descriptive notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD5FF8BB5B9FED2FD75FEC9" blockId="25.[189,1398,311,373]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">
Wings with brownish darkening; hind wing with the angle between basal (
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD5FF8BB123FEDDFBB7FEEC" box="[1063,1087,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">M</emphasis>
) and cubital (
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD5FF8BB1E0FED2FA8EFEEC" box="[1252,1286,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Cu</emphasis>
) veins ca 70°, costal margin with eight, nine or ten hamuli.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD5FF8BB5EEFE79FAF0FDFF" blockId="25.[189,1400,412,579]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD5FF8BB5EEFE79FECDFE0B" bold="true" box="[234,325,412,438]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Female</emphasis>
Total body length 
<quantity id="4CAB9B70FFD5FF8BB498FE5AFDADFE64" box="[412,549,447,474]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.5">7.5–10 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFD5FF8BB73CFE5AFD1BFE64" box="[568,659,447,473]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1972,1998]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1209,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-248@24.[189,1398,1209,1934]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 12. Sphecodes lasimensis Blüthgen, 1927, ♀ (PCMS). Habitus in lateral view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705348/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Head transverse, ca 1.25 times as wide as long (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFD5FF8BB1FCFE5AFAE1FE64" box="[1272,1385,447,473]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[187,230,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-111@25.[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 13. Sphecodes lasimensis Blüthgen, 1927, ♀ (PCMS). A. Head in frontal view. B. Mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705350/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
); vertex elevated with distance from top of head to upper margin of lateral ocellus approximately two lateral ocellar diameters as seen in frontal view; labrum trapezoidal, 0.7 times as long as basal width; ocello-ocular area and vertex irregularly punctate with punctures separated by 0.5–4 puncture diameters;
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2C661DFFD5FF8BB5BFF845FC2AF863" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705350" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5705350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705350/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" startId="25.[187,230,1952,1978]" targetBox="[189,1398,635,1907]" targetPageId="25">
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD5FF8BB5BFF845FC2AF863" blockId="25.[187,1399,1952,2014]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD5FF8BB5BFF845FE92F807" bold="true" box="[187,282,1952,1978]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Fig. 13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFD5FF8BB422F845FD6EF806" authority="Bluthgen, 1927" authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1927" box="[294,742,1952,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lasimensis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD5FF8BB422F845FDACF807" box="[294,548,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Sphecodes lasimensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B64FFD5FF8BB729F845FD6EF806" author="Bluthgen P." box="[557,742,1952,1979]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" pagination="23 - 112" refId="ref17172" refString="Bluthgen P. 1927. Beitrage zur Systematik der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. III. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 53 (1 / 3): 23 - 112." type="journal article" year="1927">Blüthgen, 1927</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, ♀ (PCMS). 
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD5FF8BB682F845FC13F807" bold="true" box="[902,923,1952,1978]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">A</emphasis>
. Head in frontal view. 
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD5FF8BB1B1F844FB4FF806" bold="true" box="[1205,1223,1953,1979]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">B</emphasis>
. Mesosoma in dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD5FF8BB456F826FEEFF860" bold="true" box="[338,359,1987,2013]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">C</emphasis>
. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD6FF88B5B9FEECFB2CFE6E" blockId="26.[189,1400,265,468]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">
paraocular area with dense adpressed white pubescence, but not obscuring integument, gena with sparser pubescence. Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum sparsely punctate (30–50 μm / 1–7); propodeal triangle (metapostnotum) and mesepisternum reticulate-rugose (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFD6FF88B6BAFEAAFBA5FED4" box="[958,1069,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[187,230,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-111@25.[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 13. Sphecodes lasimensis Blüthgen, 1927, ♀ (PCMS). A. Head in frontal view. B. Mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705350/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
). Metasomal terga sparsely punctate, on discs with shallow tiny punctures separated by a few diameters (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFD6FF88B164FE97FB45FE30" box="[1120,1229,370,397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[187,230,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-111@25.[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 13. Sphecodes lasimensis Blüthgen, 1927, ♀ (PCMS). A. Head in frontal view. B. Mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705350/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
); T1 marginal zone indistinctly punctate with a few tiny punctures; T2–T4 marginal zone smooth and impunctate; pygidial plate 0.5 times as wide as metabasitarsus; T1–T4 red, T5 partially brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD6FF88B5EEFE1EFD03FDA8" blockId="26.[189,1400,506,673]" box="[234,651,506,533]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFD6FF88B5EEFE1EFEA2FDA8" bold="true" box="[234,298,507,533]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">Male</emphasis>
(according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B64FFD6FF88B4D0FE1FFD0BFDA8" author="Bluthgen P." box="[468,643,506,533]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100" pagination="23 - 112" refId="ref17172" refString="Bluthgen P. 1927. Beitrage zur Systematik der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. III. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 53 (1 / 3): 23 - 112." type="journal article" year="1927">Blüthgen 1927</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFD6FF88B5B9FDFBFEEBFD1C" blockId="26.[189,1400,506,673]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">Head weakly transverse, ca 1.15 times as wide as long; vertex elevated with distance from top of head to upper margin of lateral ocellus approximately two lateral ocellar diameters as seen in frontal view. Tyloids (from F4 onward) weakly developed, semicircular across basal 1/5–⅓ of ventral surface of flagellomeres.</paragraph>
